Usage: mare [OPTION]

Tool the home computer setup. He performs various
settings in the GNU/Linux OS after installation. 
Namely:
  - configures elevated privileges for the user;
  - configures the message of the day;
  - configures packages sources and update the system;
  - configures Network Manager;
  - configures the video cards from Nvidia
  - configures the bootloader of the operating system;
  - improves system performance;
  - sets up additional packages;
  - sets up additional codecs;
  - configures the LightDM display manager.

  -s --sudo    configure elevated privileges for the user
  -m --motd    configure the message of the day
  -r --rest    do the rest of the settings and install additional
               packages and codecs

  -h --help    show this help and exit
  -v --version show version information and exit
  
Example:
  mare -m configure the message of the day
          
